    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-06-26T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-06-26T05:00:00-05:00" n="540"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d540">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/1335: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-06-26T18:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 26, 1928—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>496. Your 201, June 21 [<hi rend="italic">23</hi>], 2 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>I have now received from Dr. C. T. Wang a telegram which, although
                        garbled, apparently suggests that I hand June installment to Mr. Mei Yi-chi
                        who, he states, is now temporarily acting president of Tsing Hua
                        College.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>I am informed by one of Wang’s unofficial representatives here that Mei
                        has been appointed by the Nanking authorities in place of Stewart Yui who
                        was acting president at the time of my 476, June 19, 3 p.m.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>I have replied to Wang asking clarification of his message and inquiring
                        whether, in case the installment is to be paid to Mei, Wang will “direct
                        that it be expended in the manner now established for support of Tsing Hua
                        and Educational Mission in America.”</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>I beg to request Department’s instructions whether, in the event of
                        confirmation of Wang’s request that the installment be paid to Mei Yi-chi I
                        should pay it over against his receipt, and whether in so doing I would be
                        fully protected under the covering act of Congress and Executive
                        order.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
